  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study the investigators wish to explore the potential neuroprotective effects of
      acute oral supplementation of lycopene, a natural anti-oxidant derived from tomatoes, on
      cerebral vasospasm and autoregulation, and examine whether any improvements translate into a
      reduction of biochemical markers of vascular injury and inflammation a decrease in the
      prevalence of secondary strokes following subarachnoid haemorrhage.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
